<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Clipency | Finance OS</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/staff.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/clipency-cursor.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/clipency-polish.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <div class="staff-shell">
    <aside class="staff-sidebar">
      <a class="staff-brand" href="/">
        <img src="/assets/clipency-logo.png" alt="Clipency" />
      </a>

      <div class="staff-nav-section-label">Operations</div>
      <nav class="staff-nav">
        <a href="/admin">Command Center</a>
        <a href="/review">Reviews</a>
        <a href="/admin/campaigns">Campaigns</a>
        <a href="/admin/leads">Leads</a>
        <a href="/admin/payouts">Payouts</a>
        <a class="active" href="/admin/finance">Finance OS</a>
      </nav>

      <div class="staff-nav-section-label">Access</div>
      <nav class="staff-nav">
        <a href="/admin/users">Users</a>
        <a href="/workspace">Workspace</a>
        <a href="/dashboard">Clipper View</a>
      </nav>
    </aside>

    <main class="staff-main">
      <header class="staff-topbar">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">SECURE FINANCE LAUNCHER</div>
          <h1>Finance stays separate. Access stays effortless.</h1>
          <p>
            Open the dedicated Finance OS in a separate secure workspace for invoices, expenses, payouts, salaries, currency and financial operations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="staff-top-actions">
          <div class="staff-identity-chip">
            <span data-staff-initials>A</span>
            <div>
              <strong data-staff-name>Admin</strong>
              <small data-staff-role>admin</small>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="finance-launcher-grid">
        <article class="finance-launcher-hero">
          <div class="eyebrow">FINANCE OS</div>
          <h2>Open the finance workspace when invoices, payouts or expenses need attention.</h2>
          <p>
            Finance data stays isolated in its own Supabase project and Vercel deployment. Clipency simply gives admins a clean, controlled doorway into that workspace.
          </p>

          <div class="finance-security-list">
            <span>Separate database</span>
            <span>Separate authentication</span>
            <span>No iframe embedding</span>
            <span>No service key sharing</span>
          </div>

          <div class="review-actions">
            <a
              class="action-btn primary finance-open-btn"
              href="https://v0-clipency-finance-dashboard.vercel.app/login"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              Open Finance OS safely →
            </a>

            <a class="action-btn" href="/workspace">Return to workspace</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <aside class="finance-launcher-side">
          <div class="module-status-card">
            <span>Access model</span>
            <strong>Admin only</strong>
            <p>Only Clipency admins can access this launcher from the main workspace.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="module-status-card">
            <span>Security boundary</span>
            <strong>Separated</strong>
            <p>Finance stays independent, reducing database and auth complexity.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="module-status-card">
            <span>Recommended domain</span>
            <strong>finance.clipency.in</strong>
            <p>You can later map the Finance OS Vercel app to a premium subdomain.</p>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>

  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@supabase/supabase-js@2"></script>
  <script src="/supabaseClient.js"></script>
  <script src="/access-control.js"></script>
  <script src="/staff-common.js"></script>
  <script>
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", async () => {
      await window.ClipencyAccess.requireRole(["admin"]);
    });
  </script>
<script src="/clipency-cursor.js"></script>
<script src="/clipency-polish.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
